SIX people were killed following a collision between a taxi and a light motor vehicle on the N1 near Mookgopong in Limpopo on Tuesday afternoon, 24 May. ER24 spokesman Ross Campbell said paramedics arrived at the scene shortly before 2pm and found the light motor vehicle completely burnt out. “A taxi was found about 40 metres further from the roadway lying on its side. Five people were found with fatal injuries and were declared dead on the scene by paramedics,” said Campbell. ALSO READ: WhatsApp premium set to launch soon! He said a patient was found with critical injuries but despite the best efforts of paramedics, the patient died on the scene. “Another patient who was found to be in a critical condition was flown to hospital by medical helicopter for further medical care. The exact circumstances surrounding the incident were not known to our paramedics but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations,” said Campbell.